                    #gettingstarted
                        .mb-5
                            hr.mb-5
                            h5 Getting started
                            p.lead.text-justify The template is using Gulp to automate the development and build processes. All you should do to start your project is to open the terminal in the root directory (where the package.json file is located) and enter fallowing commands.
                        .mb-5
                            pre
                                code.language-markup
                                  |npm install -g gulp
                                  |
                                  |&lt;!-- When you&rsquo;re done, make sure you&rsquo;ve installed the rest of the theme&rsquo;s dependencies: --&gt;
                                  |
                                  |npm install
                                  |
                                  |&lt;!-- Start. Be aware that this replaces existing &quot;dist&quot; files, so proceed with caution. --&gt;
                                  |
                                  |gulp
                            p *Note. You should already have #[a(href="https://nodejs.org/en/") Node] installed in your machine to build the project.

                    #pugtemplateengine
                        .mb-5
                            hr.mb-5
                            h5 Pug template engine
                            p.lead.text-justify Pug is a high performance template engine heavily influenced by Haml and implemented with JavaScript for node and browsers. You can visit official site for #[a(href="https://pugjs.org") more info]. We strongly recommend you to use Pug.

                    #basictemplate
                        .mb-5
                            hr.mb-5
                            h5 Basic template
                            p.lead Copy the example below into a new PUG file to get started with it.
                        .mb-5
                            pre
                                code.language-pug
                                    |extends include/templates/layout
                                    |
                                    |block vars
                                    |    - var header_transparent = false;
                                    |
                                    |append css
                                    |
                                    |append content
                                    |    h1 Hello, world!

