                    #twitter
                        .mb-5
                            hr.mb-5
                            h5 Twitter
                            p.lead.text-justify The Twitter feed element uses a HTML5 data attribute called 'data-twitter' to determine which feed to display. You can enter your ID. How to do it:
                        .mb-5
                            p
                                ol
                                    li - Go to www.twitter.com and sign in as normal, go to your settings page.
                                    li - Go to "Widgets" on the left hand side.
                                    li - Create a new widget for what you need eg "user time line" or "search" etc.
                                    li - Feel free to check "exclude replies" if you don't want replies in results.
                                    li - Now go back to settings page, and then go back to widgets page and
                                    li - you should see the widget you just created. Click edit.
                                    li - Look at the URL in your web browser, you will see a long number like this: 345735908357048478
                                    li - Use this as your ID below instead!
                        .mb-5
                            pre
                                code.language-markup
                                    |&lt;!-- Twitter widget--&gt;
                                    |&lt;aside class=&quot;widget twitter-feed-widget&quot;&gt;
                                    |    &lt;div class=&quot;widget-title&quot;&gt;
                                    |        &lt;h6&gt;Twitter Feed&lt;/h6&gt;
                                    |    &lt;/div&gt;
                                    |    &lt;div class=&quot;twitter-feed&quot; data-twitter=&quot;345170787868762112&quot; data-number=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
                                    |&lt;/aside&gt;

                    #contactforms
                        .mb-5
                            hr.mb-5
                            h5 Contact Forms
                            p.lead Open «assets/php/contact.php» and make the following changes:

                        .mb-5
                            pre
                                code
                                    |// Mail settings
                                    |$to = "yourmail@here.com";
                                    |
                                    |// You can put here your email
                                    |$header = "From: noreply@neomax.com\r\n";
                        .mb-5
                            p If contact form not working:
                        .mb-5
                            pre
                                code
                                    |&lt;?php
                                    |    mail('you@yourmail.com','Test mail','The mail function is working!');
                                    |    echo 'Mail sent!';
                                    |?&gt;
                        .mb-5
                            ul
                                li 1. Save this code as mailtest.php
                                li 2. change you@yourmail.com to your e-mail address
                                li 3. upload mailtest.php to your server
                                li 4. open mailtest.php in your browser (http://yourwebsite.com/mailtest.php)
                                li 5. check your inbox to see if a test message arrived.
                            p If it works:
                            ul
                                li 1. double-check your form script for errors (like e-mail address misspelling)
                                li 2. use the same e-mail address as your form recipient
                                li 3. double-check your SPAM filters and SPAM/Junk/Bulk mailboxes
                            p If it not:
                            p Contact your host and ask them to check PHP mail() setting.

